summary: I actually really like that Anna keeps the gun in the same drawer as the bandages she ‘means’ to use to tend to Villanelle’s...
caption:
I actually really like that Anna keeps the gun in the same drawer as the bandages she ‘means’ to use to tend to Villanelle’s wounds because its such a contrast lol. She wants to kill her but at the same time it’s like, yea lemme keep the gun right in here with all this stuff because why the hell not. Then she chooses the gun but she can’t bring herself to go along with her wish because reasons and she kills herself instead so its a disaster from the beginning tbh.

And then there is Eve who does stab Villanelle but regrets it as soon as it dawns on her and it’s so funny to me because she runs and grabs the next best thing she can find which is a damn… kitchen towel. They are so chaotic.

summary: Killing Eve star makes Hollywood list
body:
Killing Eve star makes Hollywood list

Killing Eve star Jodie Comer has been named on Hollywood Reporter’s list of Rising Young Stars.

The industry magazine also has British actresses Letitia Wright [Black Panther] and Florence Pugh [The Little Drummer Girl] on their Next Gen Talent list.

The magazine describes them as those “whom everyone in the industry is clamouring to work with”.

Killing Eve was a hit in the US on BBC America before it was shown in the UK.

Comer, who is filming season two of the Phoebe Waller-Bridge drama told the magazine:

“I’ve never been a part of a show that has had this huge of a response.”

summary:
“Villanelle is extremely conscious all the time of the effect she has on
 people around her. Whereas Eve is quite the reverse,...
caption:
“Villanelle is extremely conscious all the time of the effect she has on people around her. Whereas Eve is quite the reverse, she never really thinks at all about what she looks like, or the effect that she’s having on other people.

She’s extremely sort of un-self conscious. So that’s very much reflected in their costumes. For someone like Villanelle, she thinks “putting that with that? She must be crazy”, you know, but for Eve it’s just like “oh whatever”. It’s the first thing she puts on in the morning. She sees it on a chair and she sticks it on. So, there is a terrific, dramatic contrast between these two women.”
